**I am an Echo**: Fight [an act 1-balanced version of] yourself.
**I am Complete**: Lose your heart blessings [but keep your keys].

I have mentioned the 10 max HP loss doesn't make sense anymore given how the blue key/heart blessing operates now. This event is actually pretty similar to traditional modes version. I am an echo remains an excellent choice, The upgrade all variant is now much more takeable, mark of the bloom being notoriously inflexible and punishing. Gorged is still fairly binary based on whether you have omamori/can hit two stores afterwards to remove the normalities. I am healthy isn't something you want to take, but It could save your run if something goes really wrong, and the option is nice.

I am an echo is very swingy depending on what character your playing. It's actually a very nasty fight for champ, because your natural good burst and inherent difficulty with scaling is the exact opposite of what you want when fighting traditional champ. Guardian, hexaghost, and slime boss all pretty much remain jokes (though a bad turn 2 at high health vs hexaghost can be punishing. Not a big problem if you are drafting ghost shield highly enough). Bronze automaton could be dangerous, but blockchain, frost primer or frontload (the encode card that blocks and gives the function retain) can all help you block the hyperbeam effectively. I can't remember exactly what you fight for snecko and gremlin gang, but they are probably fairly easy fights compared to the reward of a rare relic.

gremlins gives a gremlin leader where one of the gremlins on her first summon is gremlin nob
